# Getting your DNS
Search namecheap.com to find your name for your website, once your on the website choose a name that is within your price range.
Once the payment is done click the little drop down to the right top of the page then go onto account.
Go all the way to the bottom of the page and you should see an option to manage your website name.
To your left your going to see an option that says domain list.
Find your DNS and select manage after that you will have the option to do many things what you wanna do is select advanced DNS.
Now create a new record and make sure its an A type record and enter all the neccessary information that is needed.
Make sure you make two records one for "www" and one for "@".
After all this check your website to see if it was successful or not.
